C({"name": "steal.static.less", "type": "function", "parents": ["steal.static"], "comment": "<p>Lets you build and compile [http://lesscss.org/ Less ] css styles.</p>\n<p>Less is an extension of CSS that adds variables, mixins, and quite a bit more.\nYou can write css like:\n</p>\n\n<pre><code class='css'>@brand_color: #4D926F;\n#header {\n  color: @brand_color;\n}\nh2 {\n  color: @brand_color;\n}</code></pre><h2>Use</h2>\n\n\n<p>First, create a less file like:</p>\n\n<pre><code class='css'>@my_color red\n\nbody { color:  @my_color; }</code></pre><p>Save this in a file named <code>red.less</code>.</p>\n<p>Next, you have to require the <code>steal/less</code> plugin and then use\nsteal.less to load your less style:\n</p>\n\n\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>steal('steal/less').then(function(){\n  steal.less('red');\n});</code></pre>\n\n<p>Loads Less files relative to the current file.  It's expected that all\nLess files end with <code>less</code>.</p>\n<p>Lets you build and compile [http://lesscss.org/ Less ] css styles.</p>\n<p>Less is an extension of CSS that adds variables, mixins, and quite a bit more.\nYou can write css like:\n</p>\n\n<pre><code class='css'>@brand_color: #4D926F;\n#header {\n  color: @brand_color;\n}\nh2 {\n  color: @brand_color;\n}</code></pre><h2>Use</h2>\n\n<p>First, create a less file like:</p>\n\n<pre><code class='css'>@my_color red\n\nbody { color:  @my_color; }</code></pre><p>Save this in a file named <code>red.less</code>.</p>\n<p>Next, you have to require the <code>steal/less</code> plugin and then use\nsteal.less to load your less style:\n</p>\n\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>steal('steal/less').then(function(){\n  steal.less('red');\n});</code></pre>\n\n<p>Loads Less files relative to the current file.  It's expected that all\nLess files end with <code>less</code>.</p>", "plugin": "steal/less", "params": {"path": {"order": 0, "description": "<p>the relative path from the current file to the less file.\nYou can pass multiple paths.</p>", "name": "path", "type": "String+", "optional": false}}, "ret": {"description": "<p>returns the steal function.</p>", "type": "steal"}, "src": "../steal/less/less.js", "children": []})